        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical/Historical Information </head>
            <p>Thomas Jefferson (April 13, 1743 – July 4, 1826) was the third President of the
                United States (1801–1809), the principal author of the Declaration of Independence
                (1776), and one of the most influential Founding Fathers for his promotion of the
                ideals of republicanism in the United States. </p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>Concerns moving the Virginia capital from Williamsburg to Richmond. Suggests that the
                Board of Trade adjourn and asks that vessels be prepared by April 7 to move presses,
                books, papers and other items for the offices of Trade, Council, War, the auditors
                and registers, and for the furniture of the Capital and Palace. An armed vessel will
                transport the Treasury. </p>
        </scopecontent>
